==Old English==
===Etymology===
From ''[[god#Old English|gōd]]'' ‘good’ + ''[[spel]]'' ‘news’, translating ecclesiastical Latin ''[[bona]] [[annuntiato]]'', itself a literal rendering of ecclesiastical Latin ''[[evangelium]]'', Greek ''[[εὐαγγέλιον]]'' ‘evangel’.  The first element was (as in other Germanic languages) later associated with ''[[god#Old English|god]]'' ‘God’.

